blocks.text: The following analysis may help you understand your MAIN PROCESS FLOWS.  A first analysis can be performed using the "Process Discovery" widget, shown below, to investigate how many events and execution paths are performed. Additionally, you can switch to the "Cycle Time" metric to see which execution paths take more time during the execution.

The process execution path analysis enables you to better understand how your process is executed. The process paths on top of our reference process model stress the primary process flows. In addition, you find your Best-Run Scores for the different execution steps below. You can use this to prioritize your process improvements.

dataSource.query:
SELECT 
    count(case_id) FILTER (WHERE "event_name" MATCHES ((
		'Create debit memo manually via single transaction VF01' |
        'Create debit memo via manual billing due processing' |
        'Create debit memo automatically'
	))) / count(case_id) * 100
FROM THIS_PROCESS

SELECT 
    count(case_id) FILTER (WHERE "event_name" MATCHES ((
		'Post debit memo automatically to FI' |
        'Post debit memo to FI after block' 
	))) / count(case_id) * 100
FROM THIS_PROCESS

SELECT 
    count(case_id) FILTER (WHERE "event_name" MATCHES ((
		'Clear FI-AR item via payment run F110' |
        'Clear FI-AR item via transaction FB05' 
	))) / count(case_id) * 100
    
FROM THIS_PROCESS

SELECT 
	"1 - Main - Company Code (BUKRS)" AS "Company Code",
    count(1) AS "Number of Cases",
	COUNT (CASE_ID) FILTER (WHERE "event_name" MATCHES ((
		'Create debit memo manually via single transaction VF01' |
        'Create debit memo via manual billing due processing' |
        'Create debit memo automatically'
	))) / COUNT (CASE_ID) * 100 AS "Best-Run Score: Debit Memo Creation (%)",
    
    count(case_id) FILTER (WHERE "event_name" MATCHES ((
		'Post debit memo automatically to FI' |
        'Post debit memo to FI after block' 
	))) / count(case_id) * 100 AS "Best-Run Score: Debit Memo Posting (%)",
    
    count(case_id) FILTER (WHERE "event_name" MATCHES ((
		'Clear FI-AR item via payment run F110' |
        'Clear FI-AR item via transaction FB05' 
	))) / count(case_id) * 100 AS "Best-Run Score: FI-AR Clearing (%)"
FROM THIS_PROCESS
GROUP BY 1
ORDER BY 2 DESC
